Description:
Private Cottage On Almost 1 Acre With A Creek
Perfectly located down a quiet country lane and like something out of the pages of a children’s storybook, this character filled log cabin sits beautifully amongst a secluded setting that features a canopy of leafy established trees and offers a wonderful atmosphere for relaxed living. Spend your leisure time making the most of the meandering creek that winds its way through the property, many happy hours can be spent with family and friends taking in the sights and sounds of nature. The home has loads of charm with shady verandah to sit back on and a decked area for outdoor entertaining. Inside offers 2 spacious bedrooms, large bathroom and picture windows that frame a garden view from every angle. Open plan living area features cosy wood fire, high ceilings, chunky timbers and split system heating/cooling to ensure year round comfort. The streamlined timber kitchen has plenty of cupboards, dishwasher, hotplates and wall oven. A perfect place for quiet contemplation, the property would also allow the creative juices to flow for an artist or writer or for those wanting a self-sufficient lifestyle there is plenty of space to grow. A double garage with concrete floor, power and remote access completes a picture perfect package.
Due to strong market conditions, please call to ensure open for inspection is going ahead.
Insights: 2 Tymon Road, Cockatoo VIC 3781 was last sold in 2017.

Description:
Historic Weatherboard
I am so proud to present this character weatherboard to the market. There are so many character elements that make this the picture perfect dream home. Picket fences, an arch of roses at the front gate, privet hedges, the contrast of red brick & weatherboard. A sympathetic "Scandi" renovation and master-suite extension takes it to a whole other level of “YES!” There is even a separate 4th bedroom with own veranda, ensuite and robe which would work for guests, a teen or even as an AirB&B. All on a clear sunny 1422m2 block with a 11m x 8.7m American Barn style shed with 3-Phase Power.
Inside, the colour palette makes for a warm and homely atmosphere with the natural stained timber floors & country-style kitchen adding to the period charm. A particular feature is the working Metters cast iron wood stove set centre stage in the kitchen.
The afternoon sunlight streams through the large windows at the rear into the main kitchen, dining & family lounge area. Retreat to the living for some quiet time before you drift off to heaven/bed in the recently completed master with wood panelled gabled ceiling and exposed beams.
Outside, the fully fenced rear garden is the perfect spot to unwind - a patio area for entertaining, edible forest (veggie garden), lawn & chook pen.
For more info call Katie on 0428 744 498.

Description:
Family Home on 1 ¼ Acres of Park Like Gardens!
Locals would all agree that this is arguably one of the best properties in the area. Rarely do you find such beautiful land with park like gardens and immaculately presented, split level Hills home. The land is ever so gently sloping with sweeping lawns, colourful garden beds and established trees providing shady spots in the garden. The home’s northerly aspect provides an abundance of natural light and the pitched ceilings give it a sense of space and airiness. Designed for family living, the home offers 2 living areas divided by the spacious, central kitchen which has all the mod cons including induction cooking, dishwasher and ample storage. The spacious bedrooms are located on the upper level, the Master at one end with ensuite, then there are a further 3 bedrooms, with built in robes along with the family bathroom and laundry. Features include as new timber flooring, gas ducted heating as well as a wood heater, ceiling fans, air conditioning at each end of the home and 1 kilowatt of solar keeps the power bills to a minimum. For storage and workshop needs there’s a shed with concrete floor and power and vehicles are covered with a double carport.
CALL TO ARRANGE A PRIVATE INSPECTION TODAY!
Stephen Richards 0400 100 155

Description:
***CANCELLED - Open For Inspection - Saturday 23rd September***
Set on half an acre with views to the Warburton ranges this beautiful 2 storey, 4 bedroom home is the perfect fit for that ‘Hills’ tree change you’ve been looking for.
Downstairs you will find 3 bedrooms all with built in robes, serviced by a modern family bathroom, large lounge with cozy Coonara and French doors leading out to the full length verandah that has been designed around the stunning outlook.
The kitchen is flooded with natural light from the large windows while also offering gas cooking, huge pantry, dishwasher, breakfast bar and adjoining dining area.
Upstairs is the master suite, providing fully renovated ensuite, parents retreat and study nook - all overlooking the spectacular views.
Special features include Tasmanian Oak hardwood floors throughout, split system heating and cooling, large windows, new carpet and a fresh, modern color scheme.
Outside you will find a 6x9 shed with concrete floor and Coonara, 2 driveways offering plenty of off street parking, cubby house and veggie gardens.
Surrounded by natural bushland, it is hard to believe that you are only minutes from the township of Cockatoo offering shops, eateries, public transport, parks and highly regarded schools. This property won’t last long, so call today, inspection is a must!
Due to strong market conditions, please call to ensure open for inspection is going ahead.

Description:
Renovators, Investors & First Home Buyers!
All this gem needs is a little elbow grease, a tradie with a tool belt and some styling and you have a fantastic home or investment property. The home is situated in a quiet area of Cockatoo surrounded by nature; a very tranquil lifestyle awaits the lucky successful buyer. The home is larger than you would expect, featuring 2 bedrooms, the Master with ensuite, family room, lounge with wood heater, dining room and meals area adjacent with the kitchen. The open plan kitchen has ample storage and as new freestanding oven with gas cooktop. For the entertainer there are 2 options, the built in porch at the front with views to the Warburton Ranges, or out the back there is a purpose built undercover, decked pergola with enough space for Christmas BBQ lunch with the family. The garden is established and just needs a little TLC, and there is a handy wood shed and garden shed for storage and for vehicles there is a tandem garage and the sealed drive keeps mess to a minimum. Property’s in this price range are increasingly rare to find so don’t miss out on this one.
CALL TO ARRANGE A PRIVATE INSPECTION TODAY!

Description:
Spacious Living On 1 Acre Approx.
Perfectly positioned at the rear of the property taking advantage of the stunning treetop views is this beautiful character home that needs to be seen to be truly appreciated. The spacious floor plan offers the perfect lifestyle for the growing family with large open plan living and dining area along with rumpus/media room and large study allowing for each member of the family to have their own space. There are zoned bedrooms with master at the front of the home featuring walk in robe and full ensuite and the other 4 bedrooms toward the other end of the home all serviced by a family bathroom.
In the center of the home you will find the updated kitchen boasting granite benchtops, quality stainless steel appliances, dishwasher and storage.
Special features include polished floorboards throughout, dado paneling, gas ducted heating, split system heating & cooling and beautiful verandahs to take in the views.
You will love spending time outside relaxing in the garden or taking advantage of the stone studio (equip with built in wet bar and open fire) that would be the ideal space for someone wanting to work from home, use as an art studio, mediate, entertain or one of the other endless possibilities.
Also offering the 4 car garage with 3 phase power, concrete floor, toilet and water facilities, there is a space for everybody!
With all services connected, sealed road and driveway access & within walking distance to the shops, transport & school – this is the one you have been waiting for!
Call Riley Nicholas 0488 501 218 Today!
Due to strong market conditions, please call to ensure open for inspection is going ahead.

PERFECT FOR INVESTMENT OR FIRST HOME BUYERS
Whether you are looking for an investment property, first home or downsizing look no further, this property is perfect! Situated in a very convenient location close to public transport with a bus stop at the door, the highly regarded primary school and only a short stroll to the Cockatoo township, everything you require is close at hand. The quality brick home features three good sized bedrooms, all with built in robes, light and bright kitchen with adjoining meals area/lounge dining and an additional and very spacious rumpus room. Extra features include ducted gas heating and a split system. Step outside to a covered deck that overlooks the rear garden, chicken coop, a single carport and additional off street parking. There is also a great shed perfect for the handyman. This property is a real gem!

Description:
Reserve Your Hill's Habitat
It’s a Muddy! Highly sought after mud brick homes enjoy a bit of a cult status. As well as the obvious aesthetic appeal their thermal mass keeps them cool in summer, toasty in the winter months.
Positioned on THE BEST ROAD IN COCKATOO (guess where I live?!) 25 Mountain Road boasts a meandering lit driveway past one of the two fenced paddocks. The first thing some will notice is the big shed with front carport. You’ll fit the boat in no worries. Others will be keen to look inside the house.
A simple home with 2 bedrooms and large laundry and bathroom. This could be all you need but extending would be straight-forward (STCA) either now or down the track.
Speaking of tracks. There is one directly into Mountain Road reserve. Suddenly the 5110m2 block becomes so much more. There are no neighbours to the west - only gums, ferns, a creek and native wildlife. Bliss.
A second fenced paddock down the back with a shelter.
Services = All
Heating = wood fired coonara & ducted gas heating.

Description:
Ideal First Home Owners Private Hideaway!
Ideal for first home owners; this property is located in a quiet street and set back off the road for privacy with majestic gumtrees as a backdrop. Filled with potential, the solid home offers a blank canvas to add you own style and make it the home of your dreams or for investors, it would make a solid return as a rental or potential flip property. The home consists of 3 good sized bedrooms, the Master with walk in robe and ensuite which has a 2 way entrance so it’s perfect as a powder room as well. You then have 2 living zones at either end of the home, the lounge room at the front with a cosy wood heater and garden outlook, then to the other side the central kitchen, meals area and family room with doors leading out to the rear yard. The property is set on ½ an acre with ample cleared space to create the garden of your dreams and it’s fully fenced for safety. For vehicles and the handy man there is a single lock up garage with concrete floor and power. This tidy property has a lot to offer and will be popular amongst a range of buyers so be quick to avoid disappointment.
CALL TO ARRANGE A PRIVATE INSPECTION TODAY!

Description:
THIS IS ONE OF A KIND…. ON 4 ACRES APPROX
'BELMONT' - a little slice of paradise on offer … This very unique property offers approx. 4 acres (approx) of near level cleared, and fully fenced land. The property would perfectly suit the horse enthusiast, trades person, or someone looking to enjoy the great outdoors that this life style property offers. Features include an original chook shed, which has now been converted to a huge area accommodating cars, caravans, storage facility and a great workshop. The exceptional and very established 100 year old garden also features an established orchard, chicken coop and an excellent and fully fenced vegi patch. The much loved 4 bedroom home has seen many years, with some great additions and updates over the years, and is now ready for the new owners to either re-establish or remove for a perfect site for a new home.
Rarely does an opportunity present like this…….

YOUR NEXT STATION!
The next stop on your inspection list must be this one! A home that will not disappoint, immaculately kept and presented this 3 bedroom home is a delight! Master bedroom has access to the beautiful bathroom with separate bath and shower - perfect for a young family at bath time. The home consists of ducted heating and wood heater fire place and is very much equipped for entertaining with updated kitchen that brings the home together and overlooks the large undercover deck and the flat fenced yard, perfect for the kids to play and stay out of trouble. For the tradie, there is a good size shed with attached woodshed to the rear of the property (with car access) and a separate double carport at the front. Great yard, welcoming clean home, in a quite location, connected to main sewerage and has been re-stumped you would be crazy not to have a look. All this only a short distance to all that Cockatoo and Emerald offers, with shops, cafes, schools and transport. This solid sandstone home positioned centrally on a picturesque acre lot, boasts 2 large separate living rooms one with Large coonara heating framed by feature brick wall a true centre piece of this incredible home.

Description:
When Location, Style & Sustainability is Important!
You’re going to instantly fall in love with this immaculately presented property, spacious, stylish yet fun on a quarter acre block with edible garden, a place for healthy happy kids to play and learn about sustainability. The home's location means you can walk to everything Cockatoo has to offer including shops, cafes, schools and public transport, as well as a newly opened bulk billing Doctor. The home features 4 spacious bedrooms all with built in robes, the Master with built in robe and ensuite, great sized open plan living and dining room and hostess kitchen with stainless appliances, loads of storage and ample bench space. Add to this the undercover deck with café blinds to create another living space which has a lovely elevated outlook to the tree tops beyond, a peaceful place to relax and unwind. Some features of the home include mains gas ducted heating and instantaneous hot water, double blinds on all windows to keep the heat in or heat out in summer, quality carpets and it is decorated in a stylish neutral colour palate which never goes out of date. The garden has had a lot of love and time spent in it with manicured hedging, standard roses, paved areas, raised veggie boxes, perennial berries, fruit trees and veggies planted throughout for snacking on in the summer months. To complete the picture there’s a double garage with automatic doors and internal access so you’re private and secure when you come home with the shopping. This lovely home will appeal to many, especially young families looking for a place to raise the children in a family friendly community with lots of fresh air and natural beauty. So inspect today, you won’t be disappointed.

Description:
A MUCH LOVED HOME IN PRISTINE CONDITION!
Perfectly presented and lovingly maintained, this wonderful home has a great sense of space with raked ceilings and big windows that allow garden views. Relax in front of the solid fuel fire in the family room that adjoins the updated kitchen or settle back and unwind in the living room in front of a crackling open fire. Ducted heating throughout and a reverse cycle split system ensures year round comfort. Neutral tones add modern appeal and floating timber flooring and plush carpets provide some luxury. The renovated laundry is a dream with high gloss cabinetry and inset basin. Outdoors offers plenty of room for pets, an established garden, double carport and a verandah for you to sit back on and take in the sights and sounds of nature. Added to all of this is a 4kw solar system that will help save you money while you make the most of your new home. All situated in a wonderful community that has a highly regarded primary school, shops, buses and sporting facilities.
Due to strong market conditions, please call to ensure open for inspection is going ahead.

Description:
Great Location, Walk to Everything!
Leave the car at home as you are within a short walking distance to everything the up and coming town of Cockatoo has to offer including schools, shops, cafes, public transport and medical clinic. The property is elevated offering a tranquil outlook to the tree tops beyond and has the glorious morning sun for warmth and light. The typical split level hills home offers 3 bedrooms with built in robes, the Master with ensuite, updated kitchen with dishwasher, study and meals area and the family room on the lower level has access to the undercover deck, the perfect spot for your morning coffee in the sunshine. Features of the home include floorboards, mains gas ducted heating and the ceiling fans ensure all the heat doesn’t escape to the cathedral ceiling pitch. For vehicles there is ample off street parking at the rear and the back garden is sun filed with potential for so much more. To add to this, the property has a garden shed and is fully fenced for safety. Homes such as these in this price range do not last on the market long so be quick to organise your private inspection today.

Immaculately presented and privately located this home consists of 4 bedrooms, study area, comfortable lounge/dining room, separate family room and modern country style kitchen with plenty of bench space which overlooks the meals area. A low maintenance yard with paved entertaining area plus verandah give you options to enjoy the distant views to the Gembrook hillside while listening to the birds sing. Description:
CLASSIC BEAUTY MEETS COUNTRY CHARM ON OVER 4700m2
Hidden from view and nestled on over 1 acre of completely useable land, this beautiful federation style brick home offers a wonderful rural aspect and privacy that will allow you to make the most of country living. Surrounded by exquisite established gardens, the home offers a full length verandah, a spacious open plan living area with polished timber floors providing the best in modern living and a central kitchen complete with stainless steel appliances including a 900mm stove, dishwasher, range hood and loads of bench space and cupboards making this home the ideal entertainer. There are five bedrooms, the master features a parents retreat area, walk in robe and full ensuite whilst the remaining bedrooms all have built in robes and are serviced by an up to the minute bathroom. Gas ducted heating throughout and a reverse cycle split system ensures year round comfort. Outdoors there is a fenced yard with enough room for the children and four legged friends to romp around in as well as an enormous shed that is perfect for a tradesman, handyman, hobbyist or those requiring plenty of options for an abundance of vehicles, trailers or ‘boy’s toys’. Situated within easy reach of our highly regarded Primary School, shops and cafés, the lifestyle your family deserves is right here.
Due to strong market conditions, please call to ensure open for inspection is going ahead.
